Summary

This investigation demonstrates how attackers typically progress through a web application in stages:

Reconnaissance (directory fuzzing)
Credential attack (brute force login attempts)
Exploitation (SQL injection after access is gained)

By analyzing logs, it is possible to reconstruct the full attack chain and understand attacker behavior even without seeing the full request payloads.
